Program: Outlook
Title: 09/04/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00q89fb
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 10 Apr 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the legendary American musician and producer Nile Rodgers. He's the co-founder of 70s disco band Chic and has collaborated with stars like David Bowie, Madonna and Diana Ross. He tells Matthew about his rise from being the child of heroin addicts to the top of the music industry and about his own battle with drug addiction. His book about his extraordinary life is called Le Freak, after one of his best known songs. Show less